In Node.js legacy url module, `url.resolve(from, to)`:
```javascript
exports.resolve = function resolve(source, relative) {
  return exports.resolveObject(exports.parse(source, false, true), relative) + '';
};
```

It calls `URL.parse(source, false, true)` on the source! So it re-parses the source with `parseQueryString=false`. This means the `parsedBaseUrl` object is passed to `URL.parse` which would call `.toString()` on it, giving `[object Object]`...

